title: TensorFlow Installation Import Error (Windows 10)
body:
Specifications:
Windows 10 64-bit
NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1060 6GB (I know 8GB ideal, we just want to make sure the program will work for us)
Microsoft Visual C++ 2015 Redistributable (x64) - 14.0.24215
Microsoft Visual C++ 2015 Redistributable (x86) - 14.0.23026
Python 3.5.5
Anaconda 5.2.0
TensorFlow 1.11.0 (based on this source this TF version should work. I have also been through this similar process below with 1.10.0 https://www.tensorflow.org/install/source_windows)
CUDNN 7.3.1.20
CUDA 9.0.176

Used environment creation for GPU support 
conda env create -f dlcDependenciesFORWINDOWS.yaml

Installed cython for other error that popped up
conda install -c anaconda cython

Installed TensorFlow using pip package from https://www.tensorflow.org/install/pip
When I attempted to confirm the version of TF I received the load error shown below

![screenshot](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44264369/47159796-97f68400-d2bc-11e8-97fa-7f6eb26d0e1c.PNG)
![screenshot2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44264369/47159797-97f68400-d2bc-11e8-8cd7-96b1dff339fe.PNG)

This is the first time seeing this error, I had tried to step back through my process so the post is clear. Previously, I had made it past this point and attempted to use the given line to test the connection between CUDA and TF

sess = tf.Session(config=tf.ConfigProto(log_device_placement=True))

I wish I had a screenshot of this, but essentially it gave an error that said

NameError: name 'tf' is not defined

Other details are that I have included the CUDA (D:\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v9.0\bin),
CUPTI (D:\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v9.0\extras\CUPTI\libx64), and CUDNN (D:\cudnn-9.0-windows10-x64-v7.3.1.20\cuda\bin) all in the system pathway from the advanced system settings in "This PC" properties.

I've been playing around with these for a few days now, and I feel like it must be something simple related to what version I'm using or something. Thanks for any help you can provide!
